705211f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 4th Street
705211f-a.text:
(1)
King's Highway, at the N.E. corner of West 4th Street, showing the G. Stillwell house in 1856, which was demolished in 1926. The 2 and 1/2
story house on the S.E. corner is 356 King's Highway.
April 1923.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another view.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing also in the background the'tose Marie Court'a
4-story apartment house nearing completion.
May 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
The same, viewed from West 3rd Street, showing also from right to left theEQuentin'andMaple Courts, two 4-story apartment building nearing completion.
May 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705212f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 4th Street
705212f-b.text:
(1)
359 King's Highway, at the N.E. corner of West 4th Street, showing the old Stillwell house, which was ocoupied by G. Stillwell in 1857.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing a rear view from West 3rd Street.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing the east side of the house.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
The same, south from Quentin Road to King's Highway, showing West 4th Stree, and a rear view of the Stillwell house. The row of 2-story brick fronts are on the south side of King's Highway, between
West 4th and 5th Streets.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
